Package: waiind
Type: Package
Title: Swiss Weekly Activity Index via a Dynamic Factor Model
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Philipp", "Kronenberg", email = "PhilippKronenberg@users.noreply.github.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Estimates a high-frequency GDP indicator for Switzerland, the
    Weekly Activity Index (WAI), by extracting a single dynamic factor from
    a Bayesian mixed-frequency dynamic factor model that integrates weekly,
    monthly and quarterly data. Missing and mixed-frequency observations are
    handled through data augmentation, the factor state equation includes
    stochastic volatility to capture crisis-period fluctuations, and serial
    correlation in measurement errors is removed by quasi-differencing.
    An identification restriction fixes the loading on GDP so that the
    factor is directly interpretable as weekly GDP growth. The package also
    provides tools for real-time GDP vintage handling, out-of-sample
    forecast evaluation, and the tables and plots used in the accompanying
    analysis. Methodology and empirical results are described in
    Kronenberg (2026) <doi:10.1186/s41937-026-00157-w>, which extends the
    mixed-frequency framework of Eckert, Kronenberg, Mikosch and Neuwirth
    (2025, Journal of Applied Econometrics).
